1.title: Episode #3.1
1.plot: Headlines: French designer Sonia Rykiel, has died at the age of 86. Men's shoes are driving growth for Jimmy Choo. H&M is under fire for employing 14 year old from factories in Myanmar. Gucci sets a goal for $6 billion dollars in revenue in the wake of a recent increase in sales. Finally, designer Rachel Zoe is teaming up with eBay to benefit Save the Children

2.title: Episode #3.2
2.plot: H&M Foundation launches the Second Global Changes Award for Greener Fashion Future - Attempting to re-brand, Abercrombie & Fitch has lost its luster - As GAP sales continue to slip, Banana Republic drags - Michael Kors collaborates with Google for wearable tech-line - British icons Alexander McQueen and Isabella Blow's famous friendship is getting a movie treatment

3.title: Episode #3.3
3.plot: New York Fashion Week officially kicks off in flux - Giorgio Armani invites Ricostru to show at the Armani Theatre during Milan Fashion Week - Levi Strauss and Co. appoints David Love as President of Levi Strauss Asia, Middle East and Africa - Louis Vuitton launches seven new fragrances - Apple launches new iPhone 7, 7+ and Apple Watch Series 2 and the upgraded version of Nike Watch

4.title: Episode #3.4
4.plot: Aeropostale Wins Approval in $243 Million Sale and Give 7,000 Jobs - Hugo Boss US Chief Replaces in Efforts to Revive the Brand - New Report Names Amazon as Most Social Brand, Tiffany and Co. Most Passionately Discussed - Burberry Keeps Their Crown as Industry Leader for Sustainability in the Dow Jones Sustainability Index - Mango Gets Creative in New Digital Project Campaign

5.title: Episode #3.5
5.plot: Dior Announces Hard Cover Book for their 50th Anniversary Cosmetics - An Iconic Location is Announced for Channel's 2016 Metier d'Art Show - Coach Rejuvenated for a New Generation - Lily Aldrige Named The New Face of Bulgari - Anna Wintour Hosts Fashion Fundraiser for Hilary Clinton
